         <abstract>
            <p>We derive a series expansion for $\psi(z)$ in which the terms of the expansion are simple rational functions of $z$. From a computational viewpoint, the new series is of interest in that it converges for all $z$ not necessarily real valued, and is particularly rapid for values of $z$ near the origin. From a mathematical viewpoint the series is of interest in that, although $\psi(z)$ has poles at the negative integers and zero, the series is uniformly convergent in any finite interval $a &lt; \operatorname{Re}(z) &lt; b$.</p>
          </abstract>
